name: Whirlwind of Life
description: Generative audiovisual piece audio-reactive video. The piece invites to reflect that life is not in the atoms that compose bodies; rather, life is the organization of these atoms - and each atom can be individually replaced without destroying life. Therefore, life is simultaneously long-lasting and ephemeral. It is up to each of us to see and hear life in its constant change and permanence. We must always contemplate the whirlwind of life.
